                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 7167/16.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Bliss</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Brussels</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-08-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 29, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 216.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to this legation’s Nos. 183, 197, and
                    203, of June 4, July 8, and August 10, respectively, I have the honor to report
                    that the additional act, drawn up at the recent meeting of the permanent
                    commission of the sugar convention, was signed yesterday on behalf of the
                    adhering Powers by their diplomatic representatives accredited to Belgium.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Bliss.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
